    "note": "Scores were tuned for a calm, photogenic Pocheon nature day-trip. Scenic, photo, and relax fit are maxed because the route is built for slow walks and seasonal flower photography. Senior fit and mobility-friendly fit score above-average for a Seoul day-trip because of paved paths, half-loop options, and the Art Valley monorail. Iconic landmark fit is intentionally moderate (3) because Pocheon's stops are well-loved but not at the UNESCO or Nami-Island brand level. First-time fit is also moderate because most first-time visitors prefer Suwon Hwaseong or the Gapyeong loop instead.",
    "duration_hours": 10,
    "stop_count": 3,
    "score_rationale": {
      "scenic_level": "Maxed because all three stops are visually distinct and well-curated.",
      "photo_level": "Maxed because lavender, pink muhly, evening lights, and the quarry lake all photograph extremely well.",
      "relax_level": "Maxed because pacing is slow and walking is light to moderate at every stop.",
      "iconic_landmark_fit": "3 because Pocheon's stops have strong domestic recognition but lower international name recognition than UNESCO or Gapyeong sites.",
      "first_time_fit": "3 because first-time visitors typically prioritize UNESCO or Nami-Island branded routes; Pocheon shines for repeat visitors or photo-focused travelers.",
      "active_traveler_fit": "2 because the route is intentionally calm; active travelers will find more reward in DMZ + Suspension Bridge or the Hwaseong route.",
      "small_group_fit": "Direct match: this is the route's intended format.",
      "rain_fit": "3 because Herb Island has indoor museum and bakery sections and Art Valley has a small indoor cafe, but the route is mostly outdoor."
    },
